The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Emami focus on power brands

 ALOKANANDA GHOSH

 Calcutta, March 13: Emami Limited will focus on six ?power? brands to drive sales in the current year.

 Director Aditya V. Agarwal said, ?The BoroPlus and Navratna brands have already been established. We are now focussing on increasing sales in the Sona Chandi, Mentho Plus, Fast Relief and the recently launched Healthy amp; Fair categories.?

 The city-based personal and healthcare products company also plans to start customer interaction initiatives for brand awareness at health clubs, hospitals and even truck terminals.

 Cool Oil Navratna with Amitabh Bachchan as its endorser is already a Rs 100-crore brand with a 50 per cent market share. Mentho Plus has a 13 per cent share of the Rs 200-crore pain balm market. Fast Relief, another Big B product, is currently valued at Rs 10 crore and is growing by 70 per cent in the Rs 110-crore joint ache market.

 The company has set aside Rs 10 crore for brand creation over the next two years with another Rs 2.5 crore for development and manufacturing.

 ?The focus will also be on developing the recently launched baby oil under the healthy amp; fair brand,? said Agarwal. ?We also plan to launch a range of baby care products to take on existing market leaders. During the year, this segment will bring in Rs 6 crore and grow to Rs 30 crore when the entire range of products is launched.?

 The branded baby oil segment is estimated at Rs 80 crore, while the total baby care market is around Rs 500 crore.

 Emami also plans to start a national ?Babyline? in Hindi and English that can be accessed through a toll free number. ?The service will provide help for minor ailments and suggest home remedies through a panel of experts,? said Agarwal. 




